description:
&lt;p&gt;We are embarking on an exciting phase of development of children&#39;s services as part of a multi borough clinical strategy. There is an opportunity for innovative and forward thinking children&#39;s nurses to join the Paediatric team at the Paediatric Hub and Ambulatory unit Galaxy Ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be highly motivated, enthusiastic experienced paediatric nurse, committed to the concept that children are best cared by Children&#39;s nurses in an appropriate Children&#39;s department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to have a flexible approach and work across our three hospital sites working within the Paediatric Team linking in with the Children&#39;s A&amp;E and the Children&#39;s ward enabling the post holder to enhance clinical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We enjoy close links with two universities and are keen to develop our staff, promoting both career advancement and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Rossitsa Tacheva&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Paediatric Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: rossitsa.tacheva@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0203 758 2410&lt;/p&gt;
